                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d667">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/10585: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-13T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 13, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>316. Your 795, October 11, noon. The American and British Ambassadors in Tokyo,
                    acting under authorization from their respective Governments, made separate but
                    similar representations to Japanese Government on October 4, in regard to use of
                    the International Settlement by the Japanese as a base for military operations.
                    No reply has yet been received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
